üöÄ Cloud Deployment Platform ‚Äì Overview

A scalable and fully-automated cloud deployment platform that allows users to deploy web applications directly from Git repositories.
The platform provides:

Automated builds

Global edge hosting

Serverless routing

Cost-efficient object storage

Centralized logging & management dashboard

Powered by Cloudflare R2 for storage, Cloudflare Workers for edge routing, AWS S3, and Redis for distributed job processing.

üîß Architecture Overview

The platform consists of three core services, working together to provide a seamless deployment workflow.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Upload Service (Source Ingestion)

The Upload Service handles importing a user‚Äôs GitHub repository into the system.

‚úî How it works

The user submits a GitHub repository URL.

The service clones the repository and uploads the entire source code into AWS S3.

A unique project ID is generated.

This ID is pushed into a Redis queue for processing by the Deploy Service.

üì¶ Responsibilities

Git repo cloning

Archiving and uploading project source to S3

Enqueuing new deployment jobs into Redis

Returning the deployment ID to the user

2Ô∏è‚É£ Deploy Service (Build & Deployment Pipeline)

This service processes job IDs coming from the Redis queue and performs the actual build.

‚úî How it works

The Deploy Service listens to the Redis queue.

When an ID arrives, it downloads the corresponding project source from S3.

The source is analyzed:

If it‚Äôs a React / SPA project, it is built and converted into static HTML, CSS, JS.

Any other static assets are processed as well.

The final optimized build output is uploaded back to S3 / Cloudflare R2 under the project‚Äôs deployment path.

üì¶ Responsibilities

Pulling build jobs from Redis

Downloading project source from S3

Running builds (React ‚Üí static assets)

Uploading optimized build output

Updating Redis with deployment status

3Ô∏è‚É£ Request Service (Edge Rendering & Delivery)

The Request Service is responsible for serving the deployed project to end users.

‚úî How it works

Incoming requests are routed via Cloudflare Workers.

The subdomain is parsed to determine the project ID.

The Request Service fetches the corresponding static assets from Cloudflare R2 / S3.

The correct Content-Type headers are applied.

Files are streamed back to the client quickly and efficiently.

üì¶ Responsibilities

Edge routing based on subdomain / custom domain

Fetching deployed build files from S3/R2

Serving HTML, CSS, JS, and assets

Global caching and fast response times